9 COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to S.P. 368, L.D. 835, “An Act to Allow
10 Children to Participate in Beano Games Conducted by Nonprofit Charitable Organizations”
11 Amend the bill in section 1 in subsection 5 in paragraph B in the last line (page 1, line
12 11 in L.D.) by striking out the following: "and"
13 Amend the bill in section 1 in subsection 5 by inserting after paragraph B the following:
14 'C. A prize awarded to a winner of a beano game does not exceed the value of $100
15 for any one game and the prize is not in the form of cash; and'
16 Amend the bill in section 1 in subsection 5 by relettering the paragraphs to read
17 alphabetically.
18 Amend the bill by relettering or renumbering any nonconsecutive Part letter or section
19 number to read consecutively.
20 SUMMARY
2211 This amendment adds the requirement that beano games conducted by eligible
2222 organizations under the licensing and registration exemption established in the bill must
2233 also be limited to prizes other than cash with a total value not exceeding $100 for any one
2244 game.
